    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>An exceedingly fine and even-bedded magnesian limestone, thinly stratified, quarried in the vicinity of Solnhofen, Bavaria, Germany; widely used in lithography.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Caliza magnésica extremadamente fina y de capas parejas, finamente estratificada, extraída de canteras en las cercanías de Solnhofen, Baviera, Alemania, utilizada ampliamente en litografía.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
